    <abstract><!-- can be changed via merge in the assembly -->
      <para>
        You must start &nm; after installation to configure and manage network connections.</para>
      </abstract>
  </info>
  <procedure xml:id="start-networkmanager"><title>Starting &nm;</title>
<step><para>Start &nm; using the command:</para>
<screen>&prompt.sudo;systemctl start NetworkManager</screen>
</step>
<step><para>View &nm; status using the command:</para>
  <screen>systemctl status NetworkManager</screen>
  </step>
</procedure>
<section><title>Stopping &nm;</title>
<para>You can stop &nm; during network configuration changes or to switch to manual control. You can also stop the service for troubleshooting or debugging network issues.</para>
<procedure>
  <step><para>Disable networking.</para>
    <screen>nmcli networking off</screen>
  </step>
  <step><para>Stop &nm; using the command:</para>
  <screen>&prompt.sudo;systemctl stop NetworkManager</screen>
  </step>
  <step><para>Disable &nm; from starting on boot.</para>
  <screen>&prompt.sudo; systemctl disable NetworkManager</screen></step>
  <step><para>View &nm; status using the command:</para>
  <screen>systemctl status NetworkManager</screen>
  </step>
</procedure>
</section>
</topic>
